\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!501!!110!!44!!7!!118!!29!!6!!1!!669!!147\n|}\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n===International===\nSource: <ref name=NFTprofile/><ref name=\"rsssf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/nedved-intl.html|title=Pavel Nedved \u2013 International Appearances|publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=4 March 2013}}</ref>\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"13\"|[[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]]\n|1994||1||0\n|-\n|1995||4||0\n|-\n|1996||12||2\n|-\n|1997||10||2\n|-\n|1998||3||1\n|-\n|1999||9||2\n|-\n|2000||10||4\n|-\n|2001||11||4\n|-\n|2002||6||0\n|-\n|2003||8||2\n|-\n|2004||9||0\n|-\n|2005||2||0\n|-\n|2006||6||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!91!!18\n|}\n\n==== International goals ====\n:''Scores and results list Czech Republic's goal tally first.<ref name=\"rsssf\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1 || 14 June 1996 || [[Anfield]], Liverpool || {{fb|ITA}} || '''1'''\u20130 || 2\u20131 || [[UEFA Euro 1996|Euro 1996]]\n|-\n| 2 || 18 September 1996 || [[Na St\u00ednadlech]], Teplice || {{fb|MLT}} || '''2'''\u20130 || 6\u20130 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification|1998 World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 3 || rowspan=\"2\" | 17 December 1997 || rowspan=\"2\" | [[King Fahd II Stadium]], Riyadh || rowspan=\"2\" | {{fb|UAE}} || '''2'''\u20130 || rowspan=\"2\" | 6\u20131 || rowspan=\"2\" | [[1997 FIFA Confederations Cup|1997 Confederations Cup]]\n|-\n| 4 || '''3'''\u20130\n|-\n| 5 || 14 October 1998 || Na St\u00ednadlech, Teplice || {{fb|EST}} || '''1'''\u20130 || 4\u20131 || [[UEFA Euro 2000 qualifying|Euro 2000 qualifying]]\n|-\n| 6 || rowspan=\"2\" | 4 September 1999 || rowspan=\"2\" | [[\u017dalgiris Stadium]], Vilnius || rowspan=\"2\" | {{fb|LTU}} || '''1'''\u20130 || rowspan=\"2\" | 4\u20130 || rowspan=\"