 Amar]] || 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2007\u201309, 2012 ||''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' || [[Lawrence Kutner (House)|Dr. Lawrence Kutner]] || Main role (seasons 4\u20135); guest (season 8)\n|-\n| 2011\u201312, 2014 ||''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'' || Kevin || 10 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2013 || ''[[The Big Brain Theory]]'' || Host || 8 episodes\n|-\n|''[[We Are Men]]'' || Gil Bartis || 7 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2015 || ''[[Battle Creek (TV series)|Battle Creek]]'' || Detective Fontanelle White || 11 episodes\n|-\n|''[[The Big Picture with Kal Penn]]'' || Host || 12 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2016 || ''[[New Girl]]'' || Tripp || 2 episodes\n|-\n|''[[Deadbeat (TV series)|Deadbeat]]'' || Clyde|| 13 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\u201319 ||''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]'' || Seth Wright || Main role\n|-\n| 2016\u201317 ||''[[Superhuman (game show)|Superhuman]]'' || Host ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2019 || ''[[The Big Bang Theory (TV series)|The Big Bang Theory]]'' || Dr. Campbell || 3 episodes\n|-\n|''This Giant Beast That is the Global Economy'' || Host || 8 episodes\n|-\n|''[[Sunnyside (American TV series)|Sunnyside]]'' || Garrett Modi || Main role<br />Also executive producer\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2020 || ''[[Mira, Royal Detective]]'' || Mikku || Main role<br />Voice\n|-\n|''[[It's Pony]]'' || Fred || Voice\n|-\n|''[[Blue's Clues & You!]]'' || Himself || Episode: \"Happy Birthday, Blue!\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Commons|Kal Penn}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130122072859/http://www.whitehouse.gov/administration/eop/ope/staff/Kalpen-Modi-archive Office of Public Engagement]\n* {{Twitter}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Film|United States|Television}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Penn, Kal}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category